iOS: TableViewRow.title crashes app if it is not set to a string On iOS only (didn't test Windows, but Android works) the app will crash if you pass a number to {{TableViewRow.title}}. This is a problem because since ALOY-1355 [Alloy will convert|https://github.com/appcelerator/alloy/pull/756/files#diff-ace298e00a3d12d9898391056d0c0b47R228] a string {{true|false}} to boolean and valid integers and floats to number. So if in XML you have {{<tableviewrow title="1"></tableviewrow>}} it will become a number and crash.

Unless we can resolve ALOY-1355 in a different way (as suggested: only cast if you leave away quotes around the attribute) easily/soon, we should probably just make sure {{TableViewRow.title}} can work with boolean and number values as well.

*app.js*

{code:js}
var win = Ti.UI.createWindow();
win.add(Ti.UI.createTableView({
  top: 20,
  data: [{
    title: 1         // crashes
    // title: true      crashes
    // title: '1'       works
  }]
}));
win.open();

